cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses the challenges of reproducibility in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The experiments are conducted on Atari environments, which are commonly used in computer vision research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, hence cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the variability of agents in different environments, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
